Short PINs like 4 digits (10,000 combinations) can be guessed very quickly—often in minutes or seconds with automated tools. Longer PINs, like 7 digits (10 million combinations), take much longer, potentially hours or days depending on the attacker’s tools. Complex passwords or codes with letters (like 11 characters including letters and numbers) have vastly more combinations, making them much harder to crack—possibly taking years or more. Using longer, more complex codes greatly improves security. Keywords: “PIN cracking time,” “brute force attacks,” “password strength.”